The article is a proclamation by the President of the United States, Barack Obama, declaring September 17, 2011, as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23, 2011, as Constitution Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of the Constitution as the supreme law of the land and the basis of American liberties. It emphasizes the shared ideals of liberty, equality, and justice under the law that define Americans, regardless of their background or faith. The proclamation also acknowledges the contributions of immigrants to the country and encourages ceremonies and programs to reflect on the importance of active citizenship and to reaffirm commitment to the rights and obligations of citizenship in the nation.